    {
      "field": "Backstory",
      "page": 4,
      "value": "Furyen (Fury) of the blind pass  \n\nFuryen was born into a small settlement far in the west, Tucked in a mountain pass. A small group that held too many suspicions and traditions. \n\nIt was no wonder that he was held in instant worship by the elders of Blind Pass. A child born during the lunar eclipse. A child born with shock white hair. A child born not in tears but in quiet awe with large unnaturally verdant eyes wide open, a color longer seen in their society. He was not deprived of his family, but he was given a role in society from the moment of his birth. He was raised under protection, spent his days listening to meetings of the elders, training his body, honing his skills in martial arts and swordplay. Learning the way of natural energy and how it influenced magics. He grew up distant from others with a singular purpose. He was fated and foretold, the child of the moon who would lead their people to its peak, to know a life only fit for emperors. \n\nHe did feel as though he was special. Not in the way he was being forced, but in his study he grew to understand the energy flow of the world around him. He nearly felt as though he could see it with his eyes closed. He sought only to better himself, and cared not for the politics he was submerged in. \n\nWith the hostility and tension of the coming Ley war, he secretly only cares about the preservation of Ley, and in this instance that means opposing the Iron Concord whose reach and industry strips the world of its resources. He left his home and traveled to the war front \n\nFuryen joined the Crowns forces and has spent the last few years training blindfolded and without use of blade, a decision met with heavy criticism, he seeks now to prove his power at any level, and to develop his 6th sense for the energy around him."
    },
